page.title: 08BIRDS SEEN IN LANGTOFT
page.content: BIRDS SEEN IN LANGTOFT There are 58 species of birds in Langtoft.The rarest is a Goldcrest and Scaup.Goldcrests are rare here because their habitat is coniferous woods.Scaup are rare here because they are sea ducks.The commonest is a House Sparrow and Starling.There are a lot of water birds on the pits like Goldeneye,Tufted Duck and Pochard.This is a list of species:House Sparrow, Tree Sparrow,Dunnock,Starling, Redwing,Fieldfare,Blackbird,Song Thrush,Mistle Thrush,Redwing,Swift, Collard Dove,Chaffinch,Woodpigeon, Feral pigeon,Blue Tit,Great Tit, Coal Tit,Swallow,House Martin,Sand Martin,Wren,Rook,Crow,Jackdaw,Robin, Greenfinch,Goldfinch,Kestrel,Tawny Owl,Black Headed Gull,Little Owl, Commen Gull,Mallard,Pochard,Teal, Goldeneye,Shelduck,Canada Goose,
